OL,3,CNext Scottish government needs to
OL,4,Ctackle cost of living, say Highland
OL,5,Cvoters
OL,7,FPeople living and working in Dornoch
OL,8,Fand the surrounding area rely heavily
OL,9,Fon oil to heat their homes, and more
OL,10,Fthan 60% of households are classed as
OL,11,Fliving in poverty.
OL,13,FOn top of the rising costs, a constant
OL,14,Fissue for some residents in Kyle of
OL,15,FSutherland is social isolation.
OL,17,FSome of those tackling loneliness by
OL,18,Fmeeting for a weekly cup of tea told
OL,19,Fus they don't know which party to
OL,20,Fbelieve when it comes to promises of
OL,21,Fdelivering change.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778029387
OL,3,CNext Scottish government needs to
OL,4,Ctackle cost of living, say Highland
OL,5,Cvoters
OL,7,F"The pension's not gone up - but
OL,8,Feverything else has," Greta told us.
OL,10,FGloria said: "It's quite hard to know
OL,11,Fwho to vote for, or who'll get in who
OL,12,Fwill do what they say."
OL,14,FThe Kyle of Sutherland Development
OL,15,FTrust is an organisation focused on
OL,16,Fproviding support in the area, running
OL,17,Feverything from free fitness classes
OL,18,Fto a community pantry open to all -
OL,19,Fwithout requiring proof of financial
OL,20,Fhardship.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@UO]rD@NOUtD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
